327
00:17:34,853 --> 00:17:36,218
<i>Any theories on why?</i>

328
00:17:36,288 --> 00:17:39,917
I assume you've already dismissed
the "she loves me" theory?

329
00:17:39,992 --> 00:17:41,550
<i>It's possible.</i>

330
00:17:41,627 --> 00:17:43,527
It would require the
presupposition that everything

331
00:17:43,595 --> 00:17:45,085
she's done for
the last six years

332
00:17:45,164 --> 00:17:46,995
has been completely
inconsistent with her character,

333
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:48,761
but, yeah,
it's possible.

334
00:17:48,834 --> 00:17:51,598
As we've already established, it's
also possible that you're wrong.

335
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:54,002
<i>Or there's another
explanation.</i>

336
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:58,306
<i>Since you don't have one, I'm
gonna keep looking for you.</i>

337
00:18:01,914 --> 00:18:05,782
Let him drain, then pack it with
anesthetics and sterile gauze.

338
00:18:06,985 --> 00:18:09,476
Do you have any idea
what's going on with House?

339
00:18:10,022 --> 00:18:12,388
He's trying to get
his old fellows back.

340
00:18:12,458 --> 00:18:13,982
It's called stalking.

341
00:18:14,526 --> 00:18:16,960
I am way too busy to
play officer of the court.

342
00:18:17,029 --> 00:18:20,521
That's a shame, since you're
the one who triggered this.

343
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:22,523
What do you see
in Lucas anyway?

344
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:24,660
I don't see that
it's any of your business.

345
00:18:24,736 --> 00:18:26,363
Did you think House
wouldn't find out?

346
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:27,666
You could've
at least told me,

347
00:18:27,739 --> 00:18:30,139
so I wouldn't have coached him on
how to prove his worthiness to you.

348
00:18:30,209 --> 00:18:34,805
I know you're upset with me because I
