This is very insulting. You're
apparently shocked by this,

357
00:19:06,612 --> 00:19:10,173
which means that you thought that
there was some way that we could date,

358
00:19:10,249 --> 00:19:13,514
get married, have two kids,
a dog, retire to Florida,

359
00:19:13,585 --> 00:19:15,416
all without House
finding out.

360
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:19,082
Or you thought that we
wouldn't date all that long.

361
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:21,254
The first means
you're delusional,

362
00:19:21,326 --> 00:19:23,487
the second means
I'm delusional.

363
00:19:23,562 --> 00:19:25,894
Technically, it could also mean
you thought House had matured,

364
00:19:25,964 --> 00:19:27,625
but then we're
back to your being...

365
00:19:27,699 --> 00:19:29,166
Shut up.

366
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:32,868
You're right.
I'm sorry.

367
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:35,405
I'm also flattered.

368
00:19:35,474 --> 00:19:37,567
Yeah, 'cause you acted all
cool and everything with Wilson,

369
00:19:37,643 --> 00:19:40,942
but you feel comfortable enough
with me that you can freak out.

370
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,310
That's cool.

371
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:53,181
His sinuses are clear. The
antibiotics should work this time.

372
00:19:54,793 --> 00:19:56,784
Why did you forgive me?

373
00:19:57,329 --> 00:20:01,356
I mean, I'm glad, I'm
grateful, but I'm confused.

374
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:03,628
You've been harder on the
patient than you've been on me.

375
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:09,504
The difference between you and the
patient is that you feel shame, guilt.

376
00:20:10,776 --> 00:20:13,836
That's how I know we're
gonna get through this.

377
00:20:16,114 --> 00:20:17,604
My stomach.

378
00:20:19,518 --> 00:20:21,110
It really hurts.

379
00:20:23,655 --> 00:20:25,384
His liver's failing.

380
00:20:29,828 --> 00:20:32,854
His liver's failing and his abdomen
keeps filling with fluid, so...

381
00:20:32,931 --> 00:20:34,262
It's not meningococcemia.

382
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:37,393
No matter how much you
finish each other's sentences,

383
00:20:37,469 --> 00:20:40,563
don't count on being
a diagnostic package deal.

384
00:20:40,639 --> 00:20:42,072
Patient's liver's
not working.

385
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:45,109
We don't have time
for your little team-stakes.

386
00:20:45,177 --> 00:20:48,044
Sometimes you're just
wrong.

387
00:20:48,847 --> 00:20:51,281
Something genetic, something in
his family history we overlooked?

388
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,977
History and genetics
are spotless.

389
00:20:53,051 --> 00:20:55,576
Plus, every time he had a bad
cough as a kid, he went to a doctor.

390
00:20:55,654 --> 00:20:57,519
Klatskin tumor,
obstructing his bile ducts?

391
00:20:57,589 --> 00:20:59,557
No jaundice, wouldn't
have ocular effects.

392
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:02,890
But if it's inflammation inside the
bile channels, sclerosing cholangitis.

393
00:21:02,961 --> 00:21:04,724
Could've stopped him from
producing clotting proteins,

394
00:21:04,796 --> 00:21:06,889
damaged his blood cells,
causing small strokes.

395
00:21:06,965 --> 00:21:10,901
Enough, enough! Stop
pummeling Thirteen and Taub.

396
00:21:13,238 --> 00:21:16,639
It fits. Prep the patient for an ERCP,

397
00:21:16,708 --> 00:21:19,040
see if there's any hope of
opening his blocked bile channels.

398
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:22,239
And tell them to start
looking for a liver donor.

399
00:21:23,148 --> 00:21:24,547
Dr. Chase.

400
00:21:26,051 --> 00:21:27,416
Your turn.

401
00:21:28,086 --> 00:21:30,054
So what did she say?

402
00:21:30,689 --> 00:21:34,056
She forgave me
because I feel guilty.

403
00:21:34,993 --> 00:21:36,017
That works, too.

404
00:21:36,094 --> 00:21:39,154
And now you expect me to ask
you what the "too" refers to?

405
00:21:39,231 --> 00:21:43,565
Only if you're interested. Only if
you have doubts about her answer.

406
00:21:45,937 --> 00:21:48,667
She thinks that you don't have
anything to feel guilty about

407
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:51,538
because you didn't kill anybody, I did.

408
00:21:52,878 --> 00:21:55,642
She blames me for
Dibala's murder, not you.

409
00:21:55,714 --> 00:21:57,875
You were barely involved in
that case, she knows that.

410
00:21:57,949 --> 00:22:02,079
But I created the big, bad, evil
climate that allowed it to happen.

411
00:22:02,621 --> 00:22:04,054
You're wrong.

412
00:22:04,122 --> 00:22:05,555
Powerful
counter-argument.

413
00:22:05,624 --> 00:22:09,390
Why are you doing this? Why are
you trying to screw things up?

414
00:22:09,461 --> 00:22:11,429
