00:25:26,057 --> 00:25:28,491
House doesn't
make my decisions.

475
00:25:29,394 --> 00:25:31,828
I'm in the common bile duct.

476
00:25:31,897 --> 00:25:34,092
What's that mass?
Gallstone?

477
00:25:34,799 --> 00:25:36,926
Can we magnify times five?

478
00:25:40,138 --> 00:25:42,038
That's not a gallstone.

479
00:25:43,074 --> 00:25:45,907
His liver's completely
filled with worms.

480
00:25:48,947 --> 00:25:51,711
You have strongyloides,
also known as threadworms.

481
00:25:51,783 --> 00:25:54,547
They disseminated all over your
body, causing all your symptoms.

482
00:25:54,619 --> 00:25:55,813
How'd I get a parasite?

483
00:25:55,887 --> 00:25:59,687
Most likely through sexual
activity, but we can't be sure.

484
00:26:00,659 --> 00:26:02,456
And what's the treatment?

485
00:26:02,527 --> 00:26:03,960
Two mebendazole pills.

486
00:26:05,797 --> 00:26:07,264
That's it?

487
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:10,893
You'll be fine. Your liver,
too. Go back to your lives.

488
00:26:18,076 --> 00:26:20,010
You know this is
the doctors' lounge.

489
00:26:20,078 --> 00:26:21,170
I know.

490
00:26:21,646 --> 00:26:24,911
It seemed like the place
to read doctors' notes.

491
00:26:24,983 --> 00:26:27,383
You are good at it,
by the way.

492
00:26:28,753 --> 00:26:31,017
Why are you
reading my charts?

493
00:26:31,323 --> 00:26:34,019
Because I'm worried
about my girlfriend.

494
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:37,785
Your girlfriend is
a male porn star?

495
00:26:37,862 --> 00:26:39,352
No, I'm dating Lisa Cuddy.

496
00:26:39,864 --> 00:26:41,661
Seriously?
Cool, huh?

497
00:26:41,733 --> 00:26:44,133
And if House doesn't have his
team, that'll make her miserable,

498
00:26:44,202 --> 00:26:45,794
which will make
me miserable.

499
00:26:45,870 --> 00:26:50,307
Which brings us to the fact that you
have elevated noting to an art form.

500
00:26:50,475 --> 00:26:51,635
I see the connection.

501
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:53,007
Most doctors
write "9:00 a. m. "

502
00:26:53,078 --> 00:26:54,705
If they scrub in at 9:00
or anything near it.

503
00:26:54,779 --> 00:26:59,341
You write "9:03" and you make little
notations when procedures are delayed.

504
00:26:59,551 --> 00:27:01,280
You're easily impressed.

505
00:27:01,353 --> 00:27:03,981
Well, yeah. I was.

506
00:27:04,055 --> 00:27:08,048
Until I saw that you had virtually
stopped writing them about four weeks ago.

507
00:27:08,126 --> 00:27:09,559
Been busy.
Got a backlog.

508
00:27:09,628 --> 00:27:15,191
Yeah, people with your level of
precision don't really just get backlogs.

509
00:27:17,235 --> 00:27:20,204
No one knows why
you're leaving PPTH.

510
00:27:20,271 --> 00:27:21,568
Because it's personal.

511
00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:23,365
If something happened...

512
00:27:23,441 --> 00:27:26,808
I mean, if you're leaving to get away
from something that you did, or she did,

513
00:27:26,878 --> 00:27:28,573
or both of you did...

514
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:31,810
I mean, emotionally, maybe you want
to run away, but in my experience,

515
00:27:31,883 --> 00:27:35,876
if you're staring at a pit
bull in some guy's back yard,

516
00:27:36,621 --> 00:27:39,055
you're better off staying
right where you are.

517
00:27:39,124 --> 00:27:42,389
Face the problem, that way
it can't bite you in the ass.

518
00:27:46,931 --> 00:27:49,229
Thanks for
the folksy wisdom.

519
00:27:50,669 --> 00:27:53,661
Hey, you got any dirt
on any of the other three?

520
00:27:54,039 --> 00:27:56,007
It'd really help me out.

521
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:03,443
I thought you said those
two pills was all he needed.

522
00:28:03,515 --> 00:28:04,504
Lungs are
filling with fluid.

523
00:28:04,582 --> 00:28:06,846
Suction him and
get him on oxygen.

524
00:28:12,023 --> 00:28:15,618
Patient's lungs are severely
compromised, liver's still failing.

525
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:17,719
Worms could easily
have been a coincidence.

526
00:28:17,796 --> 00:28:19,525
Almost be surprising
if he didn't have them.

527
00:28:19,597 --> 00:28:23,260
Which means it could be a hematological
problem plus cardiomyopathy.

528
00:28:23,334 --> 00:28:26,792
No. Neck veins are flat,
precordial exam was normal.

529
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:28,566
What if it's lymphoma?

530
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:31,473
Peritoneal carcinomatosis
explains the liver failure,

531
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:34,842
paraneoplastic syndrome
explains everything else.

532
00:28:36,347 --> 00:28:39,783
Lymphoma it is.
Prep him for chemo.

533
00:28:40,685 --> 00:28:43,984
Fax Taub and Thirteen the
latest update on the case.

534
00:28:47,158 --> 00:28:48,557
Seriously?

535
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:51,153
They have as much right to
know as anyone on the team.

536
00:28:51,229 --> 00:28:53,561
You either like the
diagnosis or you don't.

537
00:28:53,631 --> 00:28:57,431
If you don't, we need to keep talking.
If you do, you need to shut up.

538
00:28:57,502 --> 00:29:00,198
What we don't need
is this stupid game.

539
00:29:08,113 --> 00:29:10,104
You're mad at House,
but you're not mad at me.

540
00:29:10,181 --> 00:29:12,581
Do you want me
to be mad at you?

541
00:29:12,650 --> 00:29:14,584
You blame House,
not me.

542
00:29:14,652 --> 00:29:16,711
I'm mad at House
because he's an ass.

543
00:29:16,788 --> 00:29:19,848
And I am mad at you, but
I don't want to leave you.

544
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:23,690
What I did may be the worst thing
I ever did, it may be the best.

545
00:29:23,762 --> 00:29:26,754
I'm either a murderer or a guy
who stopped a mass murderer.

546
00:29:26,831 --> 00:29:28,856
But I did it. Me.

547
00:29:29,667 --> 00:29:32,830
And even if it destroys me,
I'd do it again today.

548
00:29:32,904 --> 00:29:34,269
You don't mean that.
This isn't you...

549
00:29:34,339 --> 00:29:39,174
I'm not running away from what I did
because you want to pretend I never did it.

550
00:29:41,546 --> 00:29:43,605
If that's how you feel,

551
00:29:46,217 --> 00:29:47,411
okay.

552
00:29:52,390 --> 00:29:55,018
My strategy is not
completely working.

553
00:29:56,528 --> 00:29:59,463
All four of them
want to work for me,

554
00:29:59,531 --> 00:30:02,728
but all four of them have reasons
why they don't want to work for me.

555
00:30:02,801 --> 00:30:07,135
How do I get them to take one from
column A and none from column B?

556
00:30:12,076 --> 00:30:13,338
Right.

557
00:30:13,411 --> 00:30:16,676
Right, by not saying anything, you're
saying that the answer's inside me?

558
00:30:16,748 --> 00:30:18,875
The answer has nothing
to do with the question.

559
00:30:18,950 --> 00:30:20,781
Then it's not
technically the answer.

560
00:30:20,852 --> 00:30:22,752
Why do you need
three of these doctors?

561
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:28,191
Because I know they're good. Other doctors
fall into the might-be-good category.

562
00:30:28,259 --> 00:30:29,920
It has nothing to do
with them being good,

563
00:30:29,994 --> 00:30:31,689
you think they're
idiots half the time.

564
00:30:31,763 --> 00:30:33,754
But they're comfortable.
You feel abandoned by Cuddy,

565
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:37,268
so you're reaching out to
people you know for comfort.

566
00:30:37,335 --> 00:30:40,930
Oh, my God, you're right.
I don't need doctors at all.

567
00:30:41,739 --> 00:30:43,730
I just need a good friend.

568
00:30:45,143 --> 00:30:46,167
Cuddy's right.

569
00:30:46,244 --> 00:30:49,179
Maybe, just maybe, if I don't
play along, you'll realize

570
00:30:49,247 --> 00:30:52,774
you can't solve a deeper
problem with a surface solution.

571
00:30:53,484 --> 00:30:57,079
Would've been more profound
if you hadn't said anything.

572
00:30:59,324 --> 00:31:00,791
You okay?

573
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:02,224
Getting through it.

574
00:31:02,293 --> 00:31:04,784
Be a lot easier once you
two are away from here.

575
00:31:04,863 --> 00:31:06,023
Yeah.

576
00:31:09,701 --> 00:31:11,396
He's peeing blood.

577
00:31:11,703 --> 00:31:12,727
BP's rising.

578
00:31:12,804 --> 00:31:13,896
Heart rate is up to 250.

579
00:31:13,972 --> 00:31:16,065
He's going into
cardiac arrest.

580
00:31:18,476 --> 00:31:20,137
Charging. Clear.

581
00:31:20,612 --> 00:31:21,636
He's bleeding out.

582
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:23,237
His body's
completely giving out.

583
00:31:23,314 --> 00:31:24,941
Charging. Clear.

584
00:31:27,018 --> 00:31:28,110
We've got him stabilized,

585
00:31:28,186 --> 00:31:30,154
but no red cells,
no white cells,

586
00:31:30,221 --> 00:31:31,711
practically no
platelets either.

587
00:31:31,789 --> 00:31:34,587
Mebendazole can cause adverse
effects, but nothing like this.

588
00:31:34,659 --> 00:31:37,253
He's been off it
since yesterday anyway.

589
00:31:38,897 --> 00:31:42,628
Long passes, wild guesses, anything.

590
00:31:42,700 --> 00:31:45,760
Hypopituitarism? Could cause
multi-organ failure if...

591
00:31:45,837 --> 00:31:48,305
If his thyroid hormone
wasn't completely normal.

592
00:31:48,373 --> 00:31:49,806
Renal cell carcinoma.

593
00:31:49,874 --> 00:31:51,307
Renal ultrasound was clean.

594
00:31:51,376 --> 00:31:53,742
I'd say aleukemic leukemia,

595
00:31:53,811 --> 00:31:55,438
marrow's not making
enough normal cells, but...

596
00:31:55,513 --> 00:31:59,244
Ablate the patient's bone
marrow, find him a donor match.

597
00:32:00,084 --> 00:32:02,279
You want to nuke
the patient's marrow?

598
00:32:02,353 --> 00:32:04,617
He had no evidence of being
anemic or immune-compromised

599
00:32:04,689 --> 00:32:06,623
when he was admitted...
Perfect white count as well.

600
00:32:06,691 --> 00:32:07,988
Ablation
could kill him,

601
00:32:08,059 --> 00:32:11,085
or leave him defenseless
against an infection that could.

602
00:32:11,162 --> 00:32:13,653
Then come up with
something better.

603
00:32:18,169 --> 00:32:21,104
He may as well die
while we're treating him.

604
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:26,467
Okay with you if I bring the
other candidates into the loop now?

605
00:32:30,181 --> 00:32:32,479
The risks,
they're really minimal.

606
00:32:32,550 --> 00:32:35,610
We'll do a series
of painless injections...

607
00:32:36,921 --> 00:32:38,286
Excuse me.

608
00:32:41,526 --> 00:32:43,050
The whole thing can be
done as an outpatient.

609
00:32:59,544 --> 00:33:01,808
You're leaving
at 11:00 a. M?

610
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:05,014
Trust me, the case
is almost over.

611
00:33:05,917 --> 00:33:08,579
Foreman told me you're
ablating the patient's marrow

612
00:33:08,653 --> 00:33:11,645
on a non-theory that
Foreman himself withdrew.

613
00:33:11,756 --> 00:33:14,088
You're gonna kill
the patient.

614
00:33:15,593 --> 00:33:17,788
Is this about
me and Lucas?

615
00:33:20,965 --> 00:33:22,865
I want alternatives
for the patient.

616
00:33:22,934 --> 00:33:24,128
So do I.

617
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:35,972
I want to be on the team.

618
00:33:42,453 --> 00:33:45,320
You think that's gonna
save your marriage?

619
00:33:48,860 --> 00:33:50,350
I don't know.

620
00:33:53,698 --> 00:33:56,030
Four candidates,
three spots.

621
00:33:57,935 --> 00:34:00,301
I got a tough decision
ahead of me.

622
00:34:24,896 --> 00:34:29,230
<i>Hi. Remy, this is Dr. Turner
from the Pennsauken Free Clinic.</i>

623
00:34:29,300 --> 00:34:32,895
<i>We all loved meeting you,
and the job's yours.</i>

624
00:34:32,970 --> 00:34:35,700
<i>Call me back,
let's pick a start date.</i>

625
00:34:51,089 --> 00:34:55,355
I want it to look natural. I
mean, much younger, but natural.

626
00:34:55,426 --> 00:34:57,451
Can you get rid of the
crow's feet altogether?

627
00:34:57,528 --> 00:34:59,621
Or is it better to
leave a trace of them?

628
00:34:59,697 --> 00:35:02,359
I don't look old enough
to have them anyway, do I?

629
00:35:02,433 --> 00:35:03,491
Absolutely.

630
00:35:03,568 --> 00:35:04,967
I do look old enough?

631
00:35:05,036 --> 00:35:06,025
No.

632
00:35:07,238 --> 00:35:10,264
I'm sorry.
Hang on a second.

633
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:20,147
Why are you here?

634
00:35:20,218 --> 00:35:24,416
Because I think we're wrong, which
means something's gonna go wrong.

635
00:35:26,691 --> 00:35:28,022
Or right.

636
00:35:28,092 --> 00:35:29,218
Takayama here.

637
00:35:29,293 --> 00:35:31,454
It's me and Thirteen,
stop the ablation.

638
00:35:34,565 --> 00:35:35,657
Because...

639
00:35:35,733 --> 00:35:36,825
<i>Those threadworms.</i>

640
00:35:36,901 --> 00:35:39,768
Why would his body have gone to
hell just hours after they were gone?

641
00:35:39,837 --> 00:35:41,896
The worms weren't hurting him,
they were helping him.

642
00:35:41,973 --> 00:35:44,237
He has extra-intestinal Crohn's.

643
00:35:44,308 --> 00:35:46,572
<i>He got it from being
raised in too clean,</i>

644
00:35:46,644 --> 00:35:48,407
<i>too overprotective
of an environment.</i>

645
00:35:48,479 --> 00:35:49,741
<i>It's the hygiene hypothesis,</i>

646
00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:52,180
<i>why there's so much autoimmune
disease in the developed world,</i>

647
00:35:52,250 --> 00:35:53,877
and almost none in
the developing world.

648
00:35:53,951 --> 00:35:56,078
<i>The worms were keeping
the Crohn's in check,</i>

649
00:35:56,154 --> 00:35:59,988
teaching his immune system what it should've
learned from eating dirt growing up.

650
00:36:00,057 --> 00:36:02,287
Once you killed them,
it started killing him.

651
00:36:03,227 --> 00:36:08,096
So his life of filth wasn't the
problem, the clean living was.

652
00:36:08,966 --> 00:36:10,729
We'll start him
on methylprednisolone.

653
00:36:10,801 --> 00:36:12,598
And some helminths.

654
00:36:14,605 --> 00:36:16,800
Worms. Cool, huh?

655
00:36:18,809 --> 00:36:20,606
Best out of three?

656
00:36:24,982 --> 00:36:27,109
<i>Have you been
a bad boy?</i>

657
00:36:31,722 --> 00:36:33,280
<i>Yeah, that's...</i>

658
00:36:38,663 --> 00:36:40,858
I want to be on the team.

659
00:36:40,932 --> 00:36:42,263
Good news for your wife.

660
00:36:43,100 --> 00:36:45,091
Thanks for the sarcasm.

661
00:36:45,169 --> 00:36:48,764
I reorganized my life
to spend more time with her,

662
00:36:48,839 --> 00:36:51,467
but apparently I don't love
her as much as I thought.

663
00:36:51,542 --> 00:36:53,442
Or you love her more.

664
00:36:54,045 --> 00:36:58,243
This job gives you the thrill you
used to find through philandering.

665
00:36:59,784 --> 00:37:01,809
Better to cheat with
a beaker and an MRI

666
00:37:01,886 --> 00:37:05,515
than one of your platinum-blonde
plastic surgery patients.

667
00:37:07,725 --> 00:37:09,386
I'll let you know.

668
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:31,079
I told House I want
to work for him again.

669
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:34,377
Stay on the team.

670
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:37,013
You were always
more into it than I was,

671
00:37:37,088 --> 00:37:39,784
more interested
in diagnostics.

672
00:37:40,524 --> 00:37:43,516
Unless House was right
about why you want out.

673
00:37:53,871 --> 00:37:55,395
Four for four.

674
00:38:02,546 --> 00:38:04,446
I was in love with you.

675
00:38:05,683 --> 00:38:07,207
I was an idiot.

676
00:38:08,019 --> 00:38:10,487
Tried to be like you,
tried to understand you,

677
00:38:10,554 --> 00:38:13,614
because I thought
I could heal you.

678
00:38:17,428 --> 00:38:19,123
You almost killed
that patient.

679
00:38:19,196 --> 00:38:21,164
If almost not saving
his life means...

680
00:38:21,232 --> 00:38:23,393
You knew the diagnosis
a long time ago.

681
00:38:23,467 --> 00:38:26,493
You risked another patient's
life to bait your old team.

682
00:38:26,570 --> 00:38:28,037
Another one?

683
00:38:28,105 --> 00:38:29,504
You did kill Dibala.

684
00:38:30,374 --> 00:38:33,366
By playing God and
teaching us to do the same.

685
00:38:33,444 --> 00:38:35,036
I taught you to think for yourselves.

686
00:38:35,112 --> 00:38:36,374
You don't even think
of them as people,

687
00:38:36,447 --> 00:38:38,972
they're just lab rats
for your little puzzles.

688
00:38:39,050 --> 00:38:40,312
You celebrate
their humanity,

689
00:38:40,384 --> 00:38:42,750
I'd rather solve those little
puzzles and save their lives.

690
00:38:42,820 --> 00:38:45,983
Motives do matter.
Lives can't come second.

691
00:38:46,057 --> 00:38:48,719
The patient is alive.
That's what matters.

692
00:38:48,793 --> 00:38:50,226
Not to you.

693
00:38:50,294 --> 00:38:54,094
All you care about is that Taub
and Thirteen fell for your game.

694
00:38:54,165 --> 00:38:57,259
You'll poison them
just like you poisoned Chase.

695
00:38:58,302 --> 00:39:02,170
Your husband killed a patient
and you're breaking up with me?

696
00:39:03,741 --> 00:39:05,265
You ruined him,

697
00:39:08,612 --> 00:39:11,342
so he can't even see
right from wrong,

698
00:39:12,583 --> 00:39:15,950
can't even see the sanctity
of a human life any more.

699
00:39:20,791 --> 00:39:24,318
I loved you,
and I loved Chase.

700
00:39:26,664 --> 00:39:28,564
I'm sorry for you both,

701
00:39:29,934 --> 00:39:32,129
for who you've
become because

702
00:39:34,505 --> 00:39:37,133
there's no way back
for either of you.

703
00:40:42,106 --> 00:40:46,440
Any idea where I can get a great
big "Mission Accomplished" banner?

704
00:40:48,712 --> 00:40:53,206
Got my sanity back, my
license back, and now...

705
00:40:54,885 --> 00:40:57,080
You're kidding.
All of them?

706
00:40:57,154 --> 00:40:58,849
Three out of four,

707
00:40:58,923 --> 00:41:01,517
which is almost as good
as four out of five.

708
00:41:01,592 --> 00:41:03,787
Who was the...
Cameron.

709
00:41:03,861 --> 00:41:06,523
Wow. I can't believe it.

710
00:41:06,597 --> 00:41:11,432
I mean, really.
I can't believe it.

711
00:41:14,171 --> 00:41:16,765
You were right, House.
Good for you.

712
00:41:17,441 --> 00:41:18,931
Yeah. It is.

713
00:41:21,512 --> 00:41:25,846
She's broken up with Chase, and
she's leaving the hospital. Still,

714
00:41:26,484 --> 00:41:28,714
three out of four
ain't bad.

